text: Palmer Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Georgia. It is a tributary to the Etowah River. Palmer Creek derives its name from Silas Palmour, a pioneer citizen of Native American (Indian) descent. A variant name is "Palmers Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Bodies of water of Dawson County, Georgia
title: Palmer Creek (Georgia)
